article.headline: Idaho State 66, University of Great  65
article.story: GREAT FALLS (AP) -- John Chapman had 16 points and 10 rebounds Saturday and Great Falls rallied to a 73-68 victory over Montana State-Northern in the final regular-season game for both teams. J.P. Geniesse added 15 points for the Argos (6-24, 3-11 Frontier). Montana State-Northern (12-17, 3-11) led 37-31 at halftime, but Great Falls shot 57 percent from the field in the second half to take the win. Anthony Owens had 13 points and 12 rebounds for Great Falls, while Rico Suazo had 12 points, including 10-of-11 free throws. Jordan Matthews led Northern with 19 points, while Cory Brothers and Cody Gillespie added 10 points each.
